snippet.title: Algebra 2 - Dividing complex numbers by multiplying by i, (8-6i) / 3i
snippet.description:
http://www.freemathvideos.com In this video tutorial I show you how to divide complex numbers.  Since complex numbers have an imaginary part which we cannot divide into other numbers we rewrite the expression by multiplying by i or the conjugate on the denominator or numerator.
(8-6i) / 3i
